h1. Details

<div class="summary">
<p>The project is hosted on "RubyForge":http://rubyforge.org/projects/gecoder, 
which also hosts the project's mailing lists, version control and issue tracker.
</p>
</div>

h2. Communication

The following mailing lists are used for communication.

<dl>
  <dt>"gecoder-users":http://rubyforge.org/mailman/listinfo/gecoder-users</dt>
  <dd>Usage questions and general Gecode/R discussion belongs here. Basically
  	anything about Gecode/R that doesn't belong in gecoder-devel goes here.</dd>
  <dt>"gecoder-devel":http://rubyforge.org/mailman/listinfo/gecoder-devel</dt>
  <dd>Discussion about the development of Gecode/R goes here.</dd>
  <dt>"gecoder-commits":http://rubyforge.org/mailman/listinfo/gecoder-commits</dt>
  <dd>Diffs of all commits to the subversion repository are sent here. Reviewing
    the code changes and sending feedback to gecoder-devel is encouraged.</dd>
</dl>

h2. Subversion

Gecode/R uses "subversion":http://subversion.tigris.org/ for revision control. 
It can be anonymously read via http at http://gecoder.rubyforge.org/svn/trunk/.
Check out the trunk using
  svn checkout svn://rubyforge.org/var/svn/gecoder/trunk gecoder

h2. Issue tracker

"The issue tracker":http://rubyforge.org/tracker/?group_id=3553 is available
from the RubyForge project page. It handles bugs, feature requests and patches.
